1. Theoretical models                                             7031 1451
 The POD code is based on the spherical optical model, the        7031 1451
distorted-wave Born approximaiton (DWBA), one-component exciton   7031 1451
preequilibrium model, and the Hauser-Feshbach-Moldauer statis-    7031 1451
tical model.  With the preequilibrium model, semi-empirical       7031 1451
pickup and knockout process can be taken into account for         7031 1451
composite-particle emission.  The gamma-ray emission from the     7031 1451
compound nucleus can be calculated within the framework of the    7031 1451
exciton model.  The code is capable of reading in particle        7031 1451
transmission coefficients calculated by separate spherical or     7031 1451
coupled-channel optical model code. In this evaluation, the OPTMAN7031 1451
/4/ code was employed for neutrons, while the ECIS code           7031 1451
/6/ was adopted for charged particles.                            7031 1451
